The BBC is an extended arm of British imperialism, and British imperialism yawning rule in double teams with Yankee imperialism. These are huge influence over -half colonial India, and after the fall of the Soviet Union, their influence has been strengthened in India. But under Modi, India has also strengthened the connections of Russian and Chinese imperialism. India is part of the BRICS collaboration(Brazil, Russia, India, China and South Africa), a trading organization that particularly served -thinny imperialism. Thus, the BBC documentary fits into an understanding of the Avimperialists' constant state of competition and collaboration, where the competition is mainly. Disappearing modi and strengthening his counterpart in the Detine Congress Party, a party that de facto belongs to the Gandhi-Nehru family dynasty, can be a good tactic about the British and Yankees, the sharpening in India will sharpen their own position. At the same time, it must be understood that the relationship China - India is also strained, with long -term boundaries and even armed clashes on the border in the near past. India Eringen imperialist, but a semi-colony, and they are mainly under Yankee imperialism.

The incident shows anyway, through the documentary, the reactionary ancient Indian state and the Hindu fascism's crowd -murderer being, and, through the authority reaction to the documentary, the degree of corruption and fascism in the country.

