# 120 Peasants occupy landowners in Chapada Diamantina - The New Democracy

Author: Gabriel Artur

Description: In the early hours of March 1, about 120 peasants occupied the Santa Maria Farm, in the municipality of Itaberaba, in the region of Chapada Diamantina (BA). A

Publish Time: 2023-03-02T16:41:47-03:00

Modified Time: 2023-03-02T16:51:23-03:00

Updated Time: 2023-03-02T16:51:23-03:00

Images: ['[Ocupacao-Mulheres-na-Bahia-1024x461-1.jpeg](https://anovademocracia.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Ocupacao-Mulheres-na-Bahia-1024x461-1.jpeg)']

Section: Luta Pela Terra

Tags: []

Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/A Nova Democracia/2023-03-02T16-41-47-03-00/Ocupacao-Mulheres-na-Bahia-1024x461-1.jpeg)Occupation mobilized about 120 peasant women in Bahia. Photo: Reproduction

At dawn on March 1, about 120 peasants occupied Fazenda Maria, in the municipality of Itaberaba, in the region of Chapada Diamantina(BA).A fazenda ocupada tem quase 2 mil hectares de terra e está abandonada. Segundoinformações do Movimento dos Trabalhadores Rurais Sem Terra (MST), the occupation is part of the national day of struggle of women without land, which has the motto “Agribusiness profits from hunger and violence. By land and democracy, women in resistance!”.

##### ** About 15 thousand peasants fight on Earth in February **

The and reported that late January and early February was marked by peasant mobilizations in the state of Bahia. On January 30, February 13, about 2,600 peasants participated in the mobilizations of land, closing highways or occupying buildings of the old state. In Valero Jequiriçá, 250 families occupied two farms. The City of Santa Cruzde Cabrália was occupied by 200 peasants(representing another 400)Pomelhores on highways and public services and the construction of a bridge. In Sento Sé, 300 peasants protested against Australian mining company Iron and demanded immediate asphalting DABA-210. In Correntina, in the Bahian Cerrado, there was a large protest against Agile and the gun. In Itabela 178 families were dumped from theirterras. Added to the new wave of occupations on 27/02, the FEATURE mobilizations in Bahia in January and February total 9,500 peasants.

Also in February, thousands of peasants occupied dozens of latifundiosprob all over Brazil during the “Red Carnival”, wave of occupations for the proceedings Movement National Fight - Campo and City(FNL)Against the crisis that plagues the Brazilian people. To date, the occupations are concentrated in Alagoas, São Paulo(in the Pontal do Paranapanema region), Mato Grosso do Sul and Paraná. Adding the two large waves of occupations, about ** 15 MILCAMPONESES participated in the peasant mobilizations in February. **

News Source: [https://anovademocracia.com.br/120-camponesas-ocupam-latifundio-na-chapada-diamantina/](https://anovademocracia.com.br/120-camponesas-ocupam-latifundio-na-chapada-diamantina/)

